.TH COGENI-LUA 7 "February 2026" "0.1.0" "cogeni Manual"
.SH NAME
cogeni-lua \- Lua API reference and patterns for cogeni
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBcogeni\fR environment provides a suite of modules designed for AST-driven code generation.
.SH GLOBAL VARIABLES
.TP
.B _CURRENT_FILE
Absolute path to the currently executing Lua script.
.TP
.B _FILE_EXTENSION
Extension of the currently executing script (including the dot).

.SH GLOBAL FUNCTIONS
.TP
.B async(fn, ...)
Starts a new asynchronous task.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIfn\fR (function): The function to run asynchronously.
.br
\fI...\fR (any): Arguments to pass to the function.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
userdata A job handle.
.RE
.TP
.B await(job)
Pauses until a job completes.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIjob\fR (userdata): The job handle to wait for.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
... any The results of the async function.
.RE
.TP
.B sleep(seconds)
Pauses execution for a duration.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIseconds\fR (number): The number of seconds to sleep.
.br
.RE
.TP
.B write(id, content)
Buffers text for a specific output block.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIid\fR (string): The block ID.
.br
\fIcontent\fR (string): The content to write.
.br
.RE
.SH MODULES
.SS cogeni
.TP
.B cogeni.get_grammar(ext)
Looks up a grammar name by file extension.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIext\fR (string): The file extension (including dot).
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
string The grammar name.
.RE
.TP
.B cogeni.outfile(id, path)
Redirects write(id) to a file.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIid\fR (string): The block ID.
.br
\fIpath\fR (string): The file path to overwrite.
.br
.RE
.TP
.B cogeni.outtag(id, path, tag)
Redirects write(id) to a specific tag in a file.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIid\fR (string): The block ID.
.br
\fIpath\fR (string): The file path.
.br
\fItag\fR (string): The tag in the file.
.br
.RE
.TP
.B cogeni.process(path)
Triggers the generation lifecycle for a file.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIpath\fR (string): The file path.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
boolean True on success.
.RE
.TP
.B cogeni.read_ast(source, language)
Parses source code into a detailed AST.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIsource\fR (string|table): File path or handle.
.br
\fIlanguage\fR (string): The grammar name (e.g. "go", "python").
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
table The AST table.
.RE
.TP
.B cogeni.register_grammar(name, url, opts)
Registers a custom grammar source URL.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIname\fR (string): The grammar name.
.br
\fIurl\fR (string): The git repository URL.
.br
\fIopts\fR (table): Options (branch, build_cmd, artifact).
.br
.RE
.SS fs
.TP
.B fs.basedir(path)
Returns the directory of a path.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIpath\fR (string): The file path.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
string The directory part of the path.
.RE
.TP
.B fs.basename(path)
Returns the last element of a path.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIpath\fR (string): The file path.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
string The file name.
.RE
.TP
.B fs.find(dir, options)
Recursively finds files and directories.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIdir\fR (string): The starting directory.
.br
\fIoptions\fR (table): Filters (type="f"|"d", name="glob", maxdepth=N).
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
table A table where keys are paths and values are 'true'.
.RE
.TP
.B fs.join(...)
Joins multiple path elements.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fI...\fR (string): Path elements to join.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
string The joined path.
.RE
.SS jq
.TP
.B jq.query(val, query)
Executes a JQ query against a Lua value.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIval\fR (any): The value to query (usually an AST table).
.br
\fIquery\fR (string): The JQ query string.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
any|table A single result or a table of results, or nil.
.RE
.SS json
.TP
.B json.decode(str)
Decodes a JSON string into a Lua table.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIstr\fR (string): The JSON string.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
any The decoded Lua value.
.RE
.TP
.B json.encode(val, options)
Encodes a Lua value to a JSON string.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIval\fR (any): The value to encode.
.br
\fIoptions\fR (table): Optional formatting options (e.g. {indent=true}).
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
string The JSON string.
.RE
.SS toml
.TP
.B toml.decode(str)
Decodes a TOML string into a Lua table.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIstr\fR (string): The TOML string to decode.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
any The decoded Lua value.
.RE
.TP
.B toml.encode(data)
Encodes a Lua value to a TOML string.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIdata\fR (any): The Lua value to encode.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
string The TOML string.
.RE
.SS xml
.TP
.B xml.decode(str)
Decodes an XML string into a Lua table.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIstr\fR (string): The XML string to decode.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
any The decoded Lua value.
.RE
.TP
.B xml.encode(data, options)
Encodes a Lua value to an XML string.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIdata\fR (any): The Lua value to encode.
.br
\fIoptions\fR (table|nil): Optional formatting options (e.g. {root="root_name"}).
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
string The XML string.
.RE
.SS yaml
.TP
.B yaml.decode(str)
Decodes a YAML string into a Lua table.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIstr\fR (string): The YAML string to decode.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
any The decoded Lua value (table, string, number, etc).
.RE
.TP
.B yaml.encode(data)
Encodes a Lua value to a YAML string.
.IP
\fBParameters:\fR
.RS
\fIdata\fR (any): The Lua value to encode.
.br
.RE
.IP
\fBReturns:\fR
.RS
string The YAML string.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS 1. Basic Generation
.nf
    # <cogeni>
    #   write("hello", "print('hello world')")
    # </cogeni>
    # <generated by="cogeni" id="hello">
    # </cogeni>
.fi
.SS 2. Multi-file Orchestration
.nf
    -- cogeni.lua
    local files = fs.find(".", { type = "f", name = "*.py" })
    for path, _ in pairs(files) do
        async(cogeni.process, path)
    end
.fi
.SH AST TABLE SCHEMA
Every node in the AST is a table:
.TP
.B type
Grammar-defined node name (e.g., "identifier").
.TP
.B fields
Map of named children (e.g., \fBast.fields.name\fR).
.TP
.B children
Ordered list of all sub-nodes.
.TP
.B content
Raw source text (typically only for leaf nodes).
.TP
.B start_pos, end_pos
Coordinate pairs \fB{row, col}\fR.
.SH BEST PRACTICES
.IP \(bu 2
\fBPath Resolution\fR: Always use \fBfs.join(fs.basedir(_CURRENT_FILE), ...)\fR for relative paths.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBConcurrency\fR: Use \fBasync\fR for I/O bound tasks like \fBcogeni.process\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cogeni (1)
